com.sun.tools.visualvm.core.model

Class ModelFactory<M extends Model,D extends DataSource>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sun.tools.visualvm.core.model.ModelFactory<M,D>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationTypeFactory, AttachModelFactory, DataSourceDescriptorFactory, HostOverviewFactory, JmxModelFactory, JvmFactory, JvmJvmstatModelFactory, JvmstatModelFactory, SaModelFactory

    public abstract class ModelFactory<M extends Model,D extends DataSource>
extends Object
    This is abstact factory class for getting model for datasource. It as two functions. First it serves as cache for the model associated with datasource. Second, ModelFactory uses list of ModelProviders registered via registerProvider(ModelProvider ) to determine the order of in which they are consulted to obtain the model for dataSource. First model obtained from ModelProvider is associated with dataSource and returned in the future.
    Author:
    Tomas Hurka

      • getModel

        public final M getModel(D dataSource)
        Returns model for dataSource. If model is in the cache return it, otherwise consult registered ModelProviders.
        Parameters:
        dataSource - DataSource for which Model should be returned
        Returns:
        model for dataSource or null if there is not model associated with this dataSource.

      • registerProvider

        public final boolean registerProvider(ModelProvider<M,D> newProvider)
        register new ModelProvider. Model provider can be registered only once.
        Parameters:
        newProvider - to register
        Returns:
        true if this ModelFactory does not contain registered provider.

      • priority

        public int priority()
        Default priority. Subclass of ModelFactory can implement ModelProvider. In that case such provider should be used as last provider. This is ensured by returning -1, since providers, which subclass AbstractModelProvider, return positive numbers.
        Returns:
        -1
